attribs.name: marquee
attribs.current:
Torpor is a long state of dreamless slumber, during which a Kindred quite literally sleeps like the dead.
Serious injury or hunger can force a vampire into torpor, as can a stake that punctures the heart.
The oldest vampires enter torpor voluntarily, sleeping away the centuries for reasons unknown.

attribs.name: bp_slaketext
attribs.current:
Animals & bagged blood slake no Hunger.
Humans slake full Hunger.
Must kill to reduce Hunger below 1.

attribs.name: bane_text
attribs.current: Your Caitiff Blood is too dilute to carry the legacy of an Antediluvian in the form of a Clan Bane. Nevertheless, your clanless nature ensures other Kindred view you as an outsider:  You begin with the Suspect (•) Flaw, and cannot purchase positive Status during character creation.  Moreover, you suffer a dice penalty on Social tests against fellow Kindred who know you are Caitiff equal to one-half your Bane Severity (1), rounded down to a minimum of one.

attribs.name: repeating_beliefs_-LN8Qs1CpZ4BnL22dDVN_conviction
attribs.current: You Have To Do Whatever's Necessary

attribs.name: mortal_history
attribs.current: An impulse Embrace, Ava had always had the vague understanding that something fundamental separated her from other Malkavians, and even other Kindred.  This only compounded her growing resentment, and after only five years under her Sire's wing refused to accept any more of it, leaving the city and traveling westward as far as she could go.  After capture by the Second Inquisition and a brief period of unpleasantness, Ava was assigned to return to Toronto and spy on her Sire.

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-LON8Va8Z-lgzThxa-kA_advantage_details
attribs.current: The Baroness values your coterie quite highly, but her support is unreliable: The duties of her office demand much of her time, not to mention how difficult it can be to contact her given her frequent relocations and security precautions.

attribs.name: repeating_negadvantage_-LON8ZD9mjSyLC2ZstQp_negadvantage_details
attribs.current: Frederik Scheer, elder of Clan Tremere and Camarilla seneschal of Toronto, has not ceded any part of his city to the Anarchs.  The erosion of Camarilla power has only intensified his fervor: Toronto will remain the Camarilla stronghold it always has been, whatever it takes.  Unfortunately for you, his attentions are firmly fixed on your coterie --- not only are you the baroness' most prized with two of her childer among its members, but your recent activities have proven to be a thorn in Scheer's side one too many times.

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-LOZywdCG8No-wJtucFe_advantage_details
attribs.current: You can feed from cold blood, rancid blood, and fractionated plasma. None of these provide Resonances. Ventrue may not take this Merit.

attribs.name: repeating_negadvantage_-LOZzZWWI9ASEvYt1vyR_negadvantage_details
attribs.current: You’re not good with this sect at all. You weaseled out of a boon, broke an oath, or did something similar. You can try to stay out of sight and out of mind, but unless you somehow make amends, you suffer a two-dice penalty to all Social tests involving the offended faction.

attribs.name: domain_haven
attribs.current: A small but classy apartment in Uptown Toronto in a place that values its resident's privacy.  She doesn't like it when other people are over, but will share her home if a friend happens to be in a pinch.

attribs.name: domain_hunt
attribs.current:
Her alleged preference for bagged blood is more out of force of habit than anything; now that she is allowed to tear the town up on a night off, Ava takes impish glee in drinking from drunk or high partygoers, stealing their cell phones as trophies.

[No longer relevant] Johannes Napier generally supplies the bagged blood Ava insists on feeding on, though she's unafraid to seek out alternate (bagged) sources if the need requires it.  She's aware of the movements of several blood banks, legitimate and illegal, she could potentially draw upon.

attribs.name: assets_carried
attribs.current:
Wallet with some amount of cash
Cell phone with data plan

attribs.name: assets_vehicles
attribs.current: Generally relies on public transportation, but if need be can borrow her sympathetic neighbor's car with the right excuse.  Try not to get blood on it.

attribs.name: assets_stashed
attribs.current: Surveillance equipment of some kind, maybe?  Obviously goes to some lengths to keep people from finding this.

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-LON8PtZ01Qg89BO6UiI_advantage_details
attribs.current:
On one hand, you're one of the younger Anarch coteries in Toronto.  On the other hand, the Baroness has made no secret of the esteem in which she holds you (two members being her childer certainly helps).

It's a precarious place to be in, especially among Anarchs:  The Baroness is popular, so her favour counts for a lot.  But Anarchs have never been ones to adopt Camarilla-style status based on legacy, so improving your lot in Toronto is going to require action.

attribs.name: repeating_beliefs_-LN8Qs1CpZ4BnL22dDVN_touchstone_details
attribs.current:
They share a desperate single-mindedness in striving for their goals, with the understanding that success requires sacrifice.  Ava respects this, and uses it as justification for manipulating (and yes, hurting) other people.  Harker, meanwhile, is disturbed by this understanding he shares 
Interactions are tense, with Harker constantly second-guessing her motives and Ava chafing at his abrupt behavior, seeking any kind of in.  They walk a razor's edge, and it's a race to see who can get ahead of whom first.

attribs.name: repeating_beliefs_-LN8Qx7w3Ft6ADM-BGR4_touchstone_details
attribs.current:
A polite, if nosy, neighbor who's taken interest in the melancholic new arrival.  Ava has become invested in the wellbeing of him and his young family, and has quietly solved problems for them in the past, for the sake of keeping them safe and together.  In turn, she spills her troubles and insecurities to him...not that he remembers, of course.
In interactions, Ava is her true self: tired, without the sweet facade she wears with everyone else.

attribs.name: repeating_beliefs_-LN8RBkNCiDKxvaQrCNe_touchstone_details
attribs.current: Father Partridge is a watchful guardian of his flock, and something's been picking at them.  (Poor youth in his area are part of another Vampire's herd.)  His concern for those under his care has lead him to begin attempting to investigate, and brings him dangerously close to running into the wrong people.  Ava, unwilling to let the world of the Kindred ruin even more lives, has been running quiet interference to protect him, and plans to seek out the vampire and find a way to get them to move.
